# Ingest-netting multiplicity contract (OQ3, decided 2026-07-11): per
# batch, dedup each side, annihilate the adds/removes intersection. Mirrors
# netting_dups.main.cpp batch for batch.
batch
+ m 1
end
# Duplicate retractions must not outvote the add: no-op, out stays {1}.
batch
+ m 2
- m 2
- m 2
end
# Duplicate adds must not outvote the retraction: no-op, out stays {1}.
batch
+ m 3
+ m 3
- m 3
end
# Same shapes against the PRESENT row 1: presence unchanged.
batch
+ m 1
- m 1
- m 1
end
batch
+ m 1
+ m 1
- m 1
end
# Control: genuine retraction.
batch
- m 1
end
# Plain annihilating pair on an absent row.
batch
+ m 4
- m 4
end
# Control: genuine add of the same row.
batch
+ m 4
end
# Owner's framing, second clause: the annihilating m-pair has no effect
# through the explicit channel; s(5) keeps exactly what `other` proves.
batch
+ other 5
end
batch
+ m 5
- m 5
end
# Annihilated pairs leave no explicit residue: retracting the alternate
# support takes 5 down.
batch
+ m 5
- m 5
end
batch
- other 5
end
